Fantastic question, Noor. Thank you. All right, Donnie, take it away. Tell us about Teal.

00:06:52.480 --> 00:06:57.040
It does have a good color. But anyway, hopefully it's more than that. So Teal

00:06:57.040 --> 00:07:06.399
is essentially a Shiny app, but we built a framework around Shiny app to add a lot of

00:07:06.399 --> 00:07:12.799
feature out of the box. So it's using Shiny components, it's using Shiny techniques to make

00:07:12.799 --> 00:07:18.559
a Shiny app, but with what we would like to call Teal flavors. So what are these flavors?

00:07:18.559 --> 00:07:26.399
What we're trying to achieve is accelerate on how people can create Shiny apps. So no longer,

00:07:26.399 --> 00:07:31.760
I mean, while you can make a traditional Shiny app, we want to provide more functional

00:07:32.640 --> 00:07:39.839
programming way where with a small number of code, you can make your Shiny app.

00:07:41.920 --> 00:07:46.799
Another thing that we're trying to achieve with Teal is that we want to add components that

00:07:46.799 --> 00:07:53.359
kind of important in clinical trial setting, but we also know it's important in other settings as

00:07:53.359 --> 00:08:01.839
well. One of our key features that we always try to market is that it has code reproducibility.

00:08:01.839 --> 00:08:08.079
So what that means, if you create a Teal app, you're using the modules, the prebuilt modules

00:08:08.079 --> 00:08:14.239
that we have, and you run your analysis with these modules and you see something that you like.

00:08:14.880 --> 00:08:21.359
Now, Teal was positioned an exploratory tool. So in order for you to run it through some more

00:08:21.359 --> 00:08:29.200
validated environment, what Teal can do, it will provide you the code that can reproduce

00:08:29.200 --> 00:08:36.239
what you see on your Teal app or visualization. So that's very important for us to achieve

00:08:36.239 --> 00:08:42.080
because in a pharma, this is something that we always want to do. We want to be able to

00:08:42.080 --> 00:08:49.119
reproduce our analysis. Another thing that we want to promote out of the box was our

00:08:49.119 --> 00:08:56.719
exploratory features. That means subsetting, filtering, and so on. So we, by just running

00:08:56.719 --> 00:09:04.000
a very simple Teal code to make a Teal app, the filtering, it comes out of the box. So we

00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:10.960
encapsulate this. And so this is where the object-oriented comes in. We provide some

00:09:10.960 --> 00:09:17.039
API for you to control how the filter behave of if you want to define a predefined filters,

00:09:17.039 --> 00:09:25.440
but the intricacy of it, the details about that, we just encapsulate them. So by default,

00:09:25.440 --> 00:09:32.080
you make an app, you will have filtering ability. And then we kept improving on this. We have

00:09:32.159 --> 00:09:41.440
predefined modules. We have line plot, bar plot, graph that we know quite standard. And so

00:09:41.440 --> 00:09:47.200
we provide about maybe 50 plus more modules that people can look around. And the idea is that

00:09:48.080 --> 00:09:52.719
you don't need to know on how to build a custom Teal module. We just provide,

00:09:52.719 --> 00:09:59.280
we already know a standard module that could be beneficial for your analysis. So why don't you

00:09:59.280 --> 00:10:05.919
just take that in and plug it in into your code and you can run it. There's a lot more thing that

00:10:05.919 --> 00:10:12.000
I can think of. I think we have a website about this. We also have a Shiny Life session in our

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:19.119
website, all of documentation. We try to show this, the capability of Teal in the website.

00:10:19.119 --> 00:10:25.440
We also have what we call Teal Gallery. You can Google it, teal.gallery. Maybe it's a website to

00:10:25.440 --> 00:10:32.159
show you a couple of finished product of a Teal app using synthetic data. So these are all fake

00:10:32.159 --> 00:10:40.320
data. And this is what I like about our open source Teal. So right now, like I said, it's

00:10:40.320 --> 00:10:45.520
very flexible. Everything is just Shiny module. And we're looking to several other categories

00:10:45.520 --> 00:10:52.960
that can be beneficial to other department of our team. So right now, Teal, I know it's being

00:10:52.960 --> 00:10:58.719
used very heavily in our study trial, but we also want to be used on other purposes,

00:10:58.719 --> 00:11:04.559
like medical data review and so on. So maybe this is a long answer to your question, Norbert,

00:11:04.559 --> 00:11:12.320
but Teal is a product to make you easily make a Shiny app with analysis that you need.

00:11:13.760 --> 00:11:21.119
It's a big deal. It's a big deal if you're in the life sciences space. I wanted to also

